Should we also fix the validation logic of the data freshness in ```clearDataBytes```?

```
    public boolean clearDataBytes(String fullPath, int ifVersion)
    {
        ChildData data = currentData.get(fullPath);
        if ( data != null )
        {
            if ( (ifVersion < 0) || (ifVersion == data.getStat().getVersion()) ) // should we check mzxid here too?
            {
                if ( data.getData() != null )
                {
                    currentData.replace(fullPath, data, new ChildData(data.getPath(), data.getStat(), null));
                }
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
